### 3. Implement Glow Effects (Multi-Layer Borders)

**File: `internal/ui/model_view.go`**

Add glow rendering helper:

```go
// renderGlowBorder creates a multi-layer border with glow effect
func renderGlowBorder(w int, activeColor lipgloss.Color) string {
    if w < 4 {
        return "" // Not enough space for glow
    }

    // Outer layer (dimmer)
    outerStyle := lipgloss.NewStyle().
        Border(lipgloss.RoundedBorder()).
        BorderForeground(activeColor).
        Width(w - 2)

    // Inner layer (brighter)
    innerStyle := lipgloss.NewStyle().
        Border(lipgloss.RoundedBorder()).
        BorderForeground(lipgloss.Color("#ffffff")). // Bright white/gray
        Width(w - 4)

    // Since we can't nest lipgloss styles directly, simulate with
    // layered rendering using border characters
    // For now, use simpler approach: single border with brighter foreground

    return outerStyle.Render("")
}
```

Simpler glow approach - enhance existing activeBorder:

```go
activeBorder := func(w int, col FocusColumn) lipgloss.Style {
    if w < 2 {
        w = 2
    }

    color := getActiveColor(col)

    // Add subtle background glow
    bgColor := lipgloss.Color(fmt.Sprintf("#%06x",
        0x1a0000 + // Very dark purple tint
            uint32(color.Color)*0x10))

    return lipgloss.NewStyle().
        Border(lipgloss.RoundedBorder()).
        BorderForeground(color).
        Background(bgColor). // Subtle glow
        Width(w - 2).
        Height(listHeight - 2)
}
```

Note: The above assumes color.Color field exists. Better approach:

```go
activeBorder := func(w int, col FocusColumn) lipgloss.Style {
    if w < 2 {
        w = 2
    }

    color := getActiveColor(col)

    return lipgloss.NewStyle().
        Border(lipgloss.RoundedBorder()).
        BorderForeground(color).
        Width(w - 2).
        Height(listHeight - 2)
}
```

For true glow, would need lipgloss compositing. Save for future enhancement.

### 4. Enhance Agent Status Visuals

**File: `internal/ui/sidebar.go`**

Make status dots pulse when running:

```go
// In renderAgentName
func (m SidebarModel) renderAgentName(node *domain.SidebarNode, name string, isCursor bool) string {
    if node.AgentInfo == nil {
        return name
    }

    if m.shouldApplyStyle(isCursor) {
        switch node.AgentInfo.Status {
        case domain.AgentRunning:
            // Pulsing dot for running agents
            dot := ""
            // Could make dot pulse color if we had animation state in SidebarModel
            return agentRunningStyle.Render(dot + " " + name)
        case domain.AgentFailed:
            // Failed: red dot
            return agentFailedStyle.Render(" " + name)
        case domain.AgentCompleted:
            return agentCompletedStyle.Render(" " + name)
        default:
            return agentRunningStyle.Render(" " + name)
        }
    }
    return name
}
```

